cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing and paraphrase generation using language models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to automatic paraphrase generation using machine learning techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a Transformer-based language model and denoising auto-encoder to improve the quality of paraphrases.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is possible as the paper uses neural network models for paraphrase generation.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions pre-training the model on large-scale unparallel corpus, which could involve image or video data.
